<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1808/454848-625x625.jpg" alt="Learning from negative event feedback" width="625" height="625">Nothing puts things into perspective quite like a little bit of drama or negative feedback. While the days before the event might have been spent fussing over the perfect shade of purple for the napkins, an actual problem on the day will go a long way in teaching you the value of solid preparation, a strong team, and the ability to work quickly and efficiently under pressure – and for an event manager, that’s more valuable than anything else.Read our full blog to find out what else you can learn from negative event feedback: www.wrxgrp.co.za/learning-negative-event-feedback/